oc:kn_03f61184 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When finalizing tear sheet layout" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Two-page maximum. If content exceeds 2 pages, cut sections in strict priority order: Ownership Snapshot → Comparable Transactions → Business Relationships → Capital Structure → Trading Comps peers. Never cut Business Overview, Segment Breakdown, Financial Summary core, or company M&A transactions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "IB profiles must be concise for deal context; exceeding 2 pages defeats the purpose of a quick-reference profile." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_2206b3bf a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the Business Overview section" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not paste the company description directly from data tools. Rewrite as 4-6 sentence pitchbook prose characterizing revenue model, customer base, competitive moats, and growth vectors." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A CIQ summary reads as generic; pitchbook prose must convey strategic positioning that a banker can immediately act on." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4c566706 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When formatting the M&A Activity table" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use Accent color (#2E75B6) fill with white bold text for M&A table headers — this is the only table that uses a different header color from standard #D6E4F0. M&A Activity is the signature section." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The M&A section should visually stand out on scan as the signature differentiator of this profile type." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_59e8414a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When searching for comparable sector transactions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the specific industry from Query 1 results for comparable transaction searches (e.g., 'cloud observability software M&A' not 'technology M&A')." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Broad industry searches return irrelevant comps; specific industry framing yields transaction multiples that are actually comparable." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_5e9117bf a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building Trading Comps table" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Forward (NTM) multiples are mandatory when available. Show only trailing multiples only if forward data does not exist." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Bankers price deals on forward earnings — trailing-only multiples are stale and create a significant analytical gap." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_628b4b6f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the Financial Summary table" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If LTM data is available, add an LTM column labeled 'LTM [quarter end date]' to the right of the most recent fiscal year. Fiscal-year-only views can be 6+ months stale." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Bankers work off LTM for valuation cross-checks; a fiscal-year-only view is significantly outdated." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6ca070bd a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When considering whether to add management profiles" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not include a Management Team table. S&P Global tools do not return executive data, and management names from training data will be stale." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Stale or fabricated executive names undermine the credibility of the entire document." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_8226afeb a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When segment breakdown data is missing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If segment data is unavailable, replace the segment table with 2-3 qualitative sentences describing revenue mix. Never show a blank table." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A blank table looks broken and unprofessional; qualitative description still conveys useful information." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_a70ee35d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When populating M&A Activity table with transaction values" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never downgrade a known deal value to 'Undisclosed'. Use 'Undisclosed' only when tools genuinely return no value for a transaction." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Bankers rely on accurate deal values; fabricating or suppressing known values is a data integrity violation that undermines trust in the tear sheet." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

